For example, to use p = 5: 
|-40|₅ = 1/5² because 5² divides 40; 
|-12|₅ = 1/5¹ because 5¹ divides 12 but not 25; 
|6|₅ = ∞ since no power of 5 divides 6.

Now, let's consider the set ℚp of all p-adic integers, which can be thought of as "power series" in p but with decreasing exponents, to the right:

ℤp = {… + a₋pⁿ + … + a₂p² + a₁p + a₀}

where each coefficient aᵢ is an integer from 0 to p-1.
